Events
						
						2016 Future Forward Intern Conference
					
San Jose, CA
We brought together 120+ interns from across North America to spend three sunny summer days at our San Jose headquarters. They heard from executive leaders, mingled with one another, and left inspired about the future of eBay.





































Meet a 2016 Intern
						
						Amantha L.
					
Intern | Savannah College of Art and Design
MFA, Service DesigneBay HQ, San Jose, CA USA



View Profile+



Amantha L.
Choosing eBay for my summer internship was one of the best decisions I’ve made. The company empowered me, was patient, and supported me every step of my career journey. Mentorship and guidance were some of the most powerful tools I received during my time here.My favorite part of the internship experience was the opportunity to learn so much. I’ve even been able to take what I’ve learned and pass it on to others. That’s powerful. Asking for help was never looked down upon, but encouraged and supported.



























Events
						
						Hack Week
					
San Jose, CA USA
Interns combine their knowledge, creativity and expertise to solve business challenges presented by our CEO, Devin Wenig. Recent college graduates demonstrate their skills, innovating alongside eBay engineers during the week-long hack event. They also take some time to have a little fun too!







